edu.harvard.integer.common.topology

Class Network

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.harvard.integer.common.BaseEntity
      • edu.harvard.integer.common.topology.Network
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDInterface, java.io.Serializable

    @Entity
public class Network
extends BaseEntity
    A network object is the sum of all the NetworkInfo, InterDeviceLink, and Path information within its domain.

    It describes any layer of the network hierarchy down to the physical level. At the physical level, 'discovery' will be limited.

    It will contain, potentially many adjacencies.
